Sentencas: The low cycle fatigue (LCF) properties of 24Cr ferritic stainless steel for solid oxide fuel cell interconnects were investigated.
Titulo: High temperature low cycle fatigue properties of 24Cr ferritic stainless steel for SOFC applications

Sentencas: The fatigue strength of 24Cr stainless steel decreased with increasing temperature, but the fatigue life increased at 600 degrees C and 700 degrees C.
Titulo: High temperature low cycle fatigue properties of 24Cr ferritic stainless steel for SOFC applications

Sentencas: The fatigue behavior at room temperature (RI) was characterized as cyclic hardening followed by saturation and cyclic softening while marginal cyclic hardening was observed at 600 degrees C and 700 degrees C.
Titulo: High temperature low cycle fatigue properties of 24Cr ferritic stainless steel for SOFC applications

Sentencas: The superior oxidation resistance of 24Cr stainless steel allows preventing the fatal impact of oxidation on the high-temperature fatigue life.
Titulo: High temperature low cycle fatigue properties of 24Cr ferritic stainless steel for SOFC applications

Sentencas: Microstructural analysis showed that persistent slip bands (PSBs) developed prevalently at RI but not at 600 degrees C and 700 degrees C. Such temperature-dependent microstructural difference retarded the crack initiation and prolonged fatigue life at high temperatures.
Titulo: High temperature low cycle fatigue properties of 24Cr ferritic stainless steel for SOFC applications
